Now.. this looks bad too at first.. until you do a closer inspection
This result, combined with our token cleaners (`dAN`->`JAN`)
And combined with constellation would produce pretty darn good results
Because all of the  data is actually there (`TRAVELER` , `ARMENA`, `24 dAN  2006`, `23 dAN  2011`, `340000230`)
If we know that this is a passport, things like `ONTTED   STATES   o0  AMERCA` can easily be mapped to `UNITED STATES OF AMERICA`
Since constellation tells us the semantic role of different polygons on the image
